==Obtaining==
*Make it yourself: (items required for 1 jar: 8 [[anchovies|cooked anchovies]], pestle and mortar, 1 [[vial]], 1 [[flowers]], 1 [[butterfly jar]])
*# Grind up 8 [[anchovies|cooked anchovies]] with a [[pestle and mortar]] to make 8 [[anchovy paste]].
*# Get a [[sieve]] from the [[chemist]] (requires completion of [[Druidic Ritual]]) and use it on the [[anchovy paste]] with a [[vial]] in your inventory to get [[anchovy oil]]. (Uses 8 [[anchovy paste]] per [[vial]].)
*# Use [[flowers]] with the vial; you can get flowers by planting [[mithril seeds]], or buying them from the [[Miscellania]] [[flower girl]]. [[Marigolds]] (level 2 farming), [[rosemary]] (level 11 farming) and [[nasturtiums]] (level 24 farming) can also be used. You will get [[imp repellent]]. Doing this gives you 5 experience in [[Herblore]].
*# Use the vial with the [[lamp oil still]] at the [[Chemist's House]] in [[Rimmington]]. The one in [[Dorgesh-Kaan]] does not work. The still must not have any lamp oil already in it.
*# Finally, use a [[butterfly jar]] with the [[lamp oil still]].
*Ask [[Elnock Inquisitor]] if he has any spare equipment (once only), he will give you a [[butterfly net]] and 7 empty impling jars.
*Trade Elnock one captured impling of any type for three jars.
*Use a [[jar generator]]. This uses 3% of its charges, meaning a maximum of 33 could be created by one generator.
*Cast the [[Hunter Kit (spell)|Hunter Kit]] lunar spell for a [[hunter kit]] containing an impling jar.
*Purchase from [[Elnock Inquisitor]] for 2,000 coins at a limit of 10 jars per day.

